      • setDefaultEnabled

        void setDefaultEnabled(boolean enabled)
        Sets the default enabled state for change tracking. This can be overwritten on a per-thread basis by using the method setEnabled(IDataManager, boolean).
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if change tracking should be enabled, else false

      • setDefaultMode

        void setDefaultMode(IDataChangeSupport.Mode mode)
        Sets the default change tracking mode. This can be overwritten on a per-thread basis by using the method setMode(IDataManager, Mode).
        Parameters:
        mode - The default change tracking mode

      • setEnabled

        void setEnabled(IDataManager dm,
                boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables change tracking for the given data manager. If null is passed for the parameter dm then the enabled state is set for all data managers within the current thread.
        Parameters:
        dm - The data manager
        enabled - true if change tracking should be enabled, else false

      • setMode

        void setMode(IDataManager dm,
             IDataChangeSupport.Mode mode)
        Sets the change tracking mode for the given data manager. If null is passed for the parameter dm then the change tracking mode is set for all data managers within the current thread.
        Parameters:
        dm - The data manager
        mode - The change tracking mode

        Parameters:
        dm - The data manager
